It&#39;s not working because the variables are parsed by bash before the string is send to the server. You can omit this by either use single quotes to wrap the code send, or create the function on the server with `typeset`. Note that the latter option still needs to escape the variables directly used in the string.

Single quote:
```bash
$ ssh user@server &#39; 
function exit_on_error { [ $1 -eq 0 ] || echo &quot;ERROR&quot;; }
ls filethatdoesntexist
exit_on_error $?
&#39;
```

Create command:
```bash
#! /bin/bash

function exit_on_error {
    [ $1 -eq 0 ] || echo &quot;ERROR&quot;;
}

ssh user@server &quot;
$(typeset -f exit_on_error)
ls filethatdoesnotexist
exit_on_error \$?
&quot;
exit 0
```

